Program: Discovery
Title: Tsetse flies
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx5r
Last Broadcast Date: 05 August 1998
Tsetse flies and how scientists are hoping to eradicate them. The flies cause sleeping sickness in humans and cattle, but the problem of the flies is getting worse. However the development of a repellent is giving hope to scientists. Also, what should we do when we meet an alien and the singing fish and their melodius humming. Show less